Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

lgtm. The failure cases are covered by the examples I implemented with RSA keys, and there isn't any duplicated code that doesn't need to be there (i.e. test_ECC needs it's own test case), since pyca/cryptography has different calls for different key types. Also good catch on the minimum recommended ECC key size.

Flipping to -1 on this one in light of the recent bug report:

https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1528393

We need to update this patch so that the tests and verification don't crash with OpenSSL backends that don't support various ECC curves.
